<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-10-01T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-10-01T17:00:00-05:00" n="660" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d660">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/430: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-01T17:00:00-05:00">October 1, 1934—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>141. Your telegram No. 238 of September 25, 3 p.m. Department is
                            extremely interested, and you may apprise the appropriate Brazilian
                            authorities of its interest, in the negotiations for a special exchange
                            arrangement, which you report Brazil contemplates making with Germany.
                            Please keep the Department promptly and fully informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>